name: Taco Chili from Publix®
author: Publix Aprons
summary: Take a new look at a Southwestern favorite. Here's a low-maintenance recipe that's perfect for creating a lot of flavor in two easy steps. And this savory dish only gets better as a leftover.
ingredients: 2 (10 ounce) cans diced tomatoes and green chiles, undrained
1 (15 ounce) can chili beans in sauce, undrained
1 (15.25 ounce) can southwest-style corn with peppers, drained
directions: Preheat large, nonstick saute pan on medium-high 2-3 minutes
Place beef in pan (wash hands); brown 5-7 minutes, stirring to crumble meat, or until no pink remains
Stir in  ; remove meat from pan
Combine remaining ingredients in slow cooker; stir in meat
Cover and cook on HIGH 3-4 hours or LOW 6-8 hours
